A family of three was killedÂ in a head-on collision on the N2, between the Mandeni and Zinkwazi off ramps, on Saturday. The accident also left a boy, believed to be seven years old, and an older man, who had been travelling in the second vehicle, in a critical condition. Paramedics had to stabilise the injured before transferring them to hospital. It's understood that one the patients was transferred by air ambulance to the eThekwini Heart Hospital.  